newpath 0 72 moveto 504 0 rlineto 0 648 rlineto -504 0 rlineto  closepath clip newpath
0 711 moveto
10 f0
(Plum explained that the purpose of this meeting was to approve forwarding the NP proposal. Kristoffersen feels it doesn't) show
0 700 moveto
10 f0
(matter whether we have one or two NPs but it seems reasonable to move forward with one combined NP and later split it if) show
0 689 moveto
10 f0
(necessary. Simonsen feels we have enough time to decide by Dublin whether to split and that would be early enough for the) show
0 678 moveto
10 f0
(SC22 Plenary in Berlin in Summer 1999 should we deem it necessary. Glassborow said our focus should be to get the work) show
0 667 moveto
10 f0
(done and leave the issue of splitting the work until later. Plum said we seem to have the support for the combined work even) show
0 656 moveto
10 f0
(if there is not as much specific support for the portable I/O section of it. Plum feels the single NP will probably work better) show
0 645 moveto
10 f0
(from SC22's point of view regarding work on programming languages. Kristoffersen said the sense of SC22 was in favor of) show
0 634 moveto
10 f0
(embedded systems work. He feels we have expanded that to include more general performance issues. That still has support) show
0 623 moveto
10 f0
(from SC22. Plum explained what happened in the PWG sessions: we are interested in not only embedded systems but other) show
0 612 moveto
10 f0
(specific single-purpose systems and/or real-time systems. Furthermore, performance does not include floating point issues.) show
0 601 moveto
10 f0
(This will be explained in the preamble that Plum and Hayashida will write.) show
0 579 moveto
10 f0
(Plum said we understand that delegates votes here do not guarantee what the actual SC22 vote will be. Plum confirmed that) show
0 568 moveto
10 f0
(we can always split a TR in the future if we need to and that there was no guarantee that the resulting TR would look similar) show
0 557 moveto
10 f0
(to what is currently on the table in terms of the technical details.) show
0 535 moveto
10 f0
(Plum called for a formal vote to support forwarding a single combined performance NP:) show
56 512.6 moveto
10 f1
(WG21: 7 in favor, 0 opposed, 1 abstain \(France\).) show
0 490.2 moveto
10 f0
(The NBs in favor were Canada, Denmark, Germany, Ireland, Japan, UK, US.) show
0 468.2 moveto
10 f0
(Plum requested that we try to draw new people to the C++ standards process whose background is embedded / real-time etc.) show
0 446.2 moveto
10 f0
(Simonsen said he had spoken to ANSI about the $18 download and ANSI felt that we should not advertise it outside the US.) show
0 435.2 moveto
10 f0
(Plum said we should therefore beware of promoting the ANSI download. Glassborow suggested we approach our own) show
0 424.2 moveto
10 f0
(National Bodies to attempt to get them to change their policy on distribution.) show
0 402.2 moveto
10 f0
(Simonsen would like WG21 to review two FCDs from WG20. We should be prepared to discuss this in Dublin. One is on) show
0 391.2 moveto
10 f0
(sorting, the other is on locale issues.) show
0 369.2 moveto
10 f0
(Glassborow feels the co-location of WG14 & WG21 has been very beneficial and wanted to extend thanks to WG14 for) show
0 358.2 moveto
10 f0
(having us around. He also said that we should consider co-location for the year 2000 \(we already have a co-located meeting) show
0 347.2 moveto
10 f0
(in Hawaii in 1999\). WG14 may be changing their meeting schedule \(to only two meetings a year\) which may make) show
0 336.2 moveto
10 f0
(co-location more difficult but we should ask for the October 2000 meeting to be co-located. Benito joined the meeting at this) show
0 325.2 moveto
10 f0
(point and said WG14 have no location decided for this yet. Simonsen said that Denmark might be able to host a meeting but) show
0 314.2 moveto
10 f0
(did not have the facilities to support the numbers associated with a co-located meeting. Glassborow felt that the co-located) show
0 303.2 moveto
10 f0
(meetings would benefit from being in the US. Simonsen said he would discuss the possibility of Denmark hosting the April) show
0 292.2 moveto
10 f0
(2000 meeting. So far Denmark is the only volunteer for hosting the April 2000. It was emphasized that this is purely tentative) show
0 281.2 moveto
10 f0
(and is not a commitment from Simonsen.) show
0 259.2 moveto
10 f0
(Plum proposed that we thank WG14 for their excellent liaison and responsiveness. Motion accepted by acclamation.) show
0 237.2 moveto
10 f0
(Benito said that the co-located meeting was also useful for WG14 but their schedule for Hawaii \(October 1999\) was not yet) show
0 226.2 moveto
10 f0
(fixed.) show
0 204.2 moveto
10 f0
(Glassborow asked if there was any more business and if not, could we adjourn. Motion to adjourn.) show
56 181.8 moveto
10 f1
(WG21: Unanimous in favor.) show
0 159.4 moveto
10 f0
(Plum adjourned the meeting at 11:18PST, 9 October, 1998.) show
pagelevel restore
showpage
